hitehead (singer)|John Whitehead]]|Jerry Cohen}}\n| extra13         = {{hlist|Missy Elliott|Charlemagne}}\n| length13        = 4:03\n\n| title14         = 2U\n| writer14        = {{hlist|Blige}}\n| extra14         = {{hlist|Griffin}}\n| length14        = 4:45\n\n| title15         = In the Meantime\n| writer15        = {{hlist|Blige|Robinson}}\n| extra15         = {{hlist|[[Rich Harrison]]}}\n| length15        = 4:14\n\n| title16         = Forever No More\n| note16          = Poem\n| writer16        = {{hlist|Blige}}\n| extra16         = {{hlist|Blige}}\n| length16        = 1:41\n\n| title17         = Testimony\n| writer17        = {{hlist|Blige|[[Michelle Bell]]|Kenny Dickerson}}\n| extra17         = {{hlist|Flav}}\n| length17        = 5:00\n}}\n{{track listing\n| headline        = Japanese bonus track\n| collapsed       = yes\n| extra_column    = Producer(s)\n| title18         = Girl From Yesterday\n| writer18        = {{hlist|Cecil Ward|Thompson}}\n| extra18         = {{hlist|Thompson}}\n| length18        = 4:37\n}}\n\n{{track listing\n| headline        = ''No More Drama'' \u2013 2002 re-release\n| collapsed       = yes\n| extra_column    = Producer(s)\n| title1          = Love\n| writer1         = {{hlist|Blige|Bruce Miller|Ron Lawrence|[[Kwam\u00e9|Kwame Holland]]}}\n| extra1          = {{hlist|Amen-Ra|[[Kwam\u00e9|K-1 Million]]}}\n| length1         = 2:46\n\n| title2          = [[Family Affair (Mary J. Blige song)|Family Affair]]\n| writer2         = {{hlist|Blige|Bruce|Camara Kambon|[[Dr. Dre|Andre Young]]|[[Mike Elizondo]]}}\n| extra2          = {{hlist|[[Dr. Dre]]}}\n| length2         = 4:28\n\n| title3          = Steal Away \n| note3           = featuring [[Pharrell Williams|Pharrell]] & Boo Bonic\n| writer3         = {{hlist|Blige|[[Pharrell Williams]]}}\n| extra3          = {{hlist|[[The Neptunes]]}}\n| length3         = 4:27\n\n| title4          = He Think I Don't Know\n| writer4         = {{hlist|[[G\u00e9rald Isaac]]}}\n| extra4          = {{hlist|[[Isaac]]}}\n| length4         = 5:37\n\n| title5          = PMS \n| note5           = Edit\n| writer5         = {{hlist|Blige|[[Terri & Monica|Terri Robinson]]|[[Terri & Monica|Tara Tillman]]|[[Chucky Thompson]]|[[Al Green]]}}\n| extra5          = {{hlist|Thompson}}\n| length5         = 4:50\n\n| title6          = [[No More Drama (song)|No More Drama]]\n| writer6         = {{hlist|[[Jimmy Jam and Terry Lewis|James Harris III]]|[[Jimmy Jam and Terry Lewis|Terry Lewis]]|Perry Botkin, Jr., Barry de Vorzon}}\n| extra6          = {{hlist|[[Jimmy Jam and Terry Lewis|Jimmy Jam]]|Lewis}}\n| length6         = 5:26\n\n| title7          = [[Rainy Dayz]]\n| note7           = featuring [[Ja Rule]]\n| writer7         = {{hlist|[[Irv Gotti|Irving Lorenzo]]|[[Jeffrey Atkins]]}}\n| extra7          = {{hlist|[[Irv Gotti]]}}\n| length7         = 4:36\n\n| title8          = Where I've Been\n| note8           = Edit featuring [[Eve (rapper)|Eve]] \n| writer8         = {{hlist|Blige|[[Eve Jeffers]]}}\n| extra8          = {{hlist|[[Swizz Beatz]]}}\n| length8         = 4:34\n\n| title9          = Beautiful Day\n| writer9         = {{hlist|Miller}}\n| extra9          = {{hlist|Kenny Flaw}}\n| length9         = 3:33\n\n| title10         = [[Dance for Me (Mary J. Blige song)|Dance for Me]]\n| note10          = featuring [[Common (rapper)|Common]]\n| writer10        = {{hlist|Blige|Miller|Lonnie Lynn|[[Sting (musician)|Sting]]}}\n| extra10         = {{hlist|[[Dame Grease]]}}\n| length10        = 3:25\n\n| title11         = [[No More Drama (song)|No More Drama]]\n| note11          = Remix featuring [[P. Diddy]]\n| writer11        = {{hlist|[[Jimmy Jam and Terry Lewis|James Harris III]]|[[Jimmy Jam and Terry Lewis|Terry Lewis]]|Perry Botkin, Jr., Barry de Vorzon|[[Sean Combs]]|[[Mario Winans]]}}\n| extra11         = {{hlist|Combs|Winans}}\n| length11        = 4:05\n\n| title12         = Flying Away\n| writer12        = {{hlist|Blige|[[Brenda Russell]]}}\n| extra12         = {{hlist|Kiyamma Griffin}}\n| length12        = 5:00\n\n| title13         = Never Been\n| writer13        = {{hlist|[[Missy Elliott]]|Henri Charlemagne|[[Gene McFadden]]|[[John Whitehead (singer)|John Whitehead]]|Jerry Cohen}}\n| extra13         = {{hlist|Missy Elliott|Charlemagne}}\n| length13        = 4:03\n\n| title14         = 2U\n| writer14        = {{hlist|Blige}}\n| extra14         = {{hlist|Griffin}}\n| length14        = 4:45\n\n| title15         = In the Meantime\n| writer15        = {{hlist|Blige|Robinson}}\n| extra15         = {{hlist|[[Rich Harrison]]}}\n| length15        = 4:14\n\n| title16         = Forever No More\n| note16          = Poem\n| writer16        = {{hlist|Blige}}\n| extra16         = {{hlist|Blige}}\n| length16        = 1:41\n\n| title17         = Testimony\n| writer17        = {{hlist|Blige|[[Michelle Bell]]|Kenny Dickerson}}\n| extra17         = {{hlist|Flav}}\n| length17        = 5:00\n}}\n{{track listing\n| headline        = International bonus track\n| collapsed       = yes\n| extra_column    = Producer(s)\n| title18         = [[Dance for Me (Mary J. Blige song)|Dance for Me]]\n| note18          = Plutonium Remix featuring [[Common (rapper)|Common]]\n| writer18        = {{hlist|Blige|Miller|Lonnie Lynn|[[Sting (musician)|Sting]]}}\n| extra18         = {{hlist|[[Dame Grease]]}}\n| length18        = 3:25\n}}\n{{track listing\n| headline        = Japanese bonus tracks\n| collapsed       = yes\n| extra_column    = Producer(s)\n| title18         = Girl from Yesterday\n| writer18        = {{hlist|Cecil Ward|Thompson}}\n| extra18         = {{hlist|Thompson}}\n| length18        = 4:37\n\n| title19         = Checkin' for Me\n| writer19        = {{hlist|Cecil Ward|Thompson}}\n| extra19         = {{hlist|Thompson}}\n| length19        = 3:06\n}}\n\n===Sample credits===\n*\"Love\" contains sample from \"[[In the Hall of the Mountain King]]\" (1875), composed by [[Edvard Grieg]].{{Citation needed|reason=none credit in liner notes|date=August 2019}}\n*\"PMS\" contains excerpts from \"[[Simply Beautiful]]\" (1972), written and performed by [[Al Green]].\n*\"No More Drama\" embodies portions of \"[[Nadia's Theme|''The Young and the Restless'' Theme]]\" (1971), written by Perry Botkin and Barry de Vorzon.\n*\"Dance for Me\" contains a sample from \"[[The Bed's Too Big Without You]]\" (1979), written by [[Sting (musician)|Sting]] and performed by [[The Police]].\n*\"Flying Away\" contains a sample from \"[[Brenda Russell (album)|God Bless You]]\" (1979), written and performed by [[Brenda Russell]].\n*\"Never Been\" contains a sample from \"Why Oh Why\" (1980), written and performed by [[McFadden & Whitehead]].\n*\"No More Drama (Remix)\" contains a sample from \"You Can't Do It Alone\" (1980), performed by [[Chic (band)|Chic]].\n*\"Checkin' for Me\" contains a sample from \"They Were Overcome (By the Word)\". performed by [[The Clark Sisters]].{{Citation needed|reason=none credit in liner notes|date=August 2019}}\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Chart (2001\u201302)\n! scope=\"col\" | Peak<br/>position\n|-\n{{albumchart|Australia|36|artist=Mary J. Blige|album=No More Drama|rowheader=true|accessdate=2016-08-19}}\n|-\n{{albumchart|Austria|17|artist=Mary J. Blige|album=No More Drama|rowheader=true|accessdate=2016-08-19}}\n|-\n{{albumchart|Flanders|32|artist=Mary J. Blige|album=No More Drama|rowheader=true|accessdate=2016-08-19}}\n|-\n{{albumchart|Wallonia|24|artist=Mary J. Blige|album=No More Drama|rowheader=true|accessdate=2016-08-19}}\n|-\n{{albumchart|BillboardCanada|5|artist=Mary J. Blige|album=No More Drama|rowheader=true|accessdate=2016-08-19}}\n|-\n{{albumchart|Denmark|10|artist=Mary J. Blige|album=No More Drama|rowheader=true|accessdate=2016-08-19}}\n|-\n{{albumchart|Netherlands|9|artist=Mary J. Blige|album=No More Drama|rowheader=true|accessdate=2016-08-19}}\n|-\n{{albumchart|France|8|artist=Mary J. Bli