}}\n|Tornado remained over open country, causing no damage.\n|-\n|bgcolor=#{{storm colour|storm}} | <big>'''EF0'''</big>\n|'''SSE of [[Carnegie, Oklahoma|Carnegie]]''' (3rd tornado)\n|[[Caddo County, Oklahoma|Caddo]]\n|{{Coord|35.01|-98.55|name=Carnegie (Apr. 13, EF0)}}\n|0150\n|{{convert|4|mi|km|}}\n|Tornado remained over open country, causing no damage.\n|-\n|colspan=\"7\" align=center| <small>Sources: [http://www.spc.noaa.gov/climo/reports/120413_rpts.html SPC Storm Reports for 04/13/12], [http://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/stormevents/ NCDC Storm Events Database]</small>\n|-\n|}\n\n===April 14 event===\n{| class=\"wikitable collapsible\" width=\"100%\"\n!colspan=\"7\"|List of reported tornadoes - Saturday, April 14, 2012\n|-\n|<center>'''[[Enhanced Fujita scale|EF#]]'''</center> || <center>'''Location'''</center> || <center>'''County'''</center> || <center>'''Coord.'''</center> || <center>'''Time (UTC)'''</center> || <center>'''Path length'''</center> || <center>'''Comments/Damage'''</center>\n|-\n|colspan=\"7\" align=center|'''[[Oklahoma]]'''\n|-\n|bgcolor=#{{storm colour|cat1}} | <big>'''EF1'''</big>\n|'''NNW of [[Mustang, Oklahoma|Mustang]]'''\n|[[Canadian County, Oklahoma|Canadian]]\n|{{Coord|35.40|-97.74|name=Mustang (Apr. 13, EF1)}}\n|0552\n|{{convert|2|mi|km|}}\n|Numerous frame homes sustained minor damage, mostly to roofs and siding, and had garage doors and windows blown out. One home sustained partial roof loss. Four mobile homes also sustained minor damage, and many trees, fences, and power lines were downed.\n|- \n|bgcolor=#{{storm colour|storm}} | <big>'''EF0'''</big>\n|'''NW of [[Woodward, Oklahoma|Woodward]]'''\n|[[Woodward County, Oklahoma|Woodward]]\n|{{Coord|36.53|-99.52|name=Woodward (Apr. 14, EF0)}}\n|2049\n|{{convert|4|mi|km|}}\n|This tornado remained over open country, causing no damage.\n|-\n|bgcolor=#{{storm colour|cat1}} | <big>'''EF1'''</big>\n|'''N of [[Woodward, Oklahoma|Woodward]]'''\n|[[Woodward County, Oklahoma|Woodward]], [[Harper County, K