n was destroyed.\n|-\n|bgcolor=#{{storm colour|storm}} | <big>'''EF0'''</big>\n|'''NW of [[Wellfleet, Nebraska|Wellfleet]] to SW of [[Brady, Nebraska|Brady]]'''\n|[[Lincoln County, Nebraska|Lincoln]]\n|{{Coord|40.84|-100.81|name=Wellfleet (Apr. 14, EF0)}}\n|2336\n|{{convert|15|mi|km|}}\n|An intermittent tornado remained over open country, causing no damage.\n|-\n|bgcolor=#{{storm colour|storm}} | <big>'''EF0'''</big>\n|'''NNW of [[Anselmo, Nebraska|Anselmo]]'''\n|[[Custer County, Nebraska|Custer]]\n|{{Coord|41.65|-99.82|name=Anselmo (Apr. 14, EF0)}}\n|0038\n|{{convert|0.1|mi|m|}}\n|Brief tornado remained over open country, causing no damage.\n|-\n|bgcolor=#{{storm colour|cat1}} | <big>'''EF1'''</big>\n|'''NNW of [[Pleasant Dale, Nebraska|Pleasant Dale]]'''\n|[[Seward County, Nebraska|Seward]]\n|{{Coord|40.86|-96.94|name=Pleasant Dale (Apr. 14, EF1)}}\n|0426\n|{{convert|2.3|mi|km|}}\n|Several outbuildings were destroyed. Homes suffered minor damage and trees were downed along the path.\n|-\n|colspan=\"7\" align=center|'''[[Iowa]]'''\n|-\n|bgcolor=#{{storm colour|storm}} | <big>'''EF0'''</big>\n|'''NW of [[Castana, Iowa|Castana]]'''\n|[[Monona County, Iowa|Monona]]\n|{{Coord|42.13|-95.99|name=Castana (Apr. 14, EF0)}}\n|1928\n|{{convert|0.4|mi|km|}}\n|Brief tornado remained over open country, causing no damage.\n|-\n|bgcolor=#{{storm colour|cat2}} | <big>'''EF2'''</big>\n|'''W of [[Percival, Iowa|Percival]] to S of [[Tabor, Iowa|Tabor]]'''\n|[[Fremont County, Iowa|Fremont]]\n|{{Coord|40.82|-95.75|name=Thurman (Apr. 14, EF2)}}\n|2235\n|{{convert|12|mi|km|}}\n|This half-mile wide wedge tornado caused significant damage in [[Thurman, Iowa|Thurman]], where 70% of the structures in town sustained some degree of damage, including 14 homes that were destroyed. Many trees were snapped or uprooted, some of which landed on homes. Four people were injured, including a semi-truck driver who was severely injured after his truck was blown off of [[Interstate 29]] and flipped. \n|-\n|bgcolor=#{{storm colour|cat2}} | <big>'''EF2'''</big>\n|'''SW of [[Cromwell, Iowa|Cromwell]] to NE of [[Creston, Iowa|Creston]]'''\n|[[Adams County, Iowa|Adams]], [[Union County, Iowa|Union]]\n|{{Coord|41.07|-94.36|name=Creston (Apr. 14, EF2)}}\n|2355\n|{{convert|16.6|mi|km|}}\n|A high-end EF2 wedge tornado struck the northwestern part of Creston, causing major damage. Multiple frame homes were severely damaged, and a few manufactured homes were completely swept away and destroyed. Apartment buildings and condominiums sustained major structural damage, and vehicles were flipped and tossed in parking lots. The Green Hills Education Agency building had total roof loss and collapse of masonry exterior walls, while the Greater Regional Medical Center also sustained major roof and exterior wall damage. The tornado inflicted significant damage to buildings at the [[Southwestern Community College (Iowa)|Southwestern Community College]] campus, and many trees were snapped or uprooted. Farmsteads outside of town also sustained damage, including one where a small and frail home was leveled. 10 people were injured. \n|-Southwestern Community College (Iowa)\n|bgcolor=#{{storm colour|cat1}} | <big>'''EF1'''</big>\n|'''E of [[New Virginia, Iowa|New Virginia]]'''\n|[[Warren County, Iowa|Warren]]\n|{{Coord|41.19|-93.67|name=New Virginia (Apr. 14, EF1)}}\n|0055\n|{{convert|1|mi|km|}}\n|This tornado flipped several camper trailers and caused major damage to farm outbuildings.\n|-\n|bgcolor=#{{storm colour|cat1}} | <big>'''EF1'''</big>\n|'''N of [[Oskaloosa, Iowa|Oskaloosa]]'''\n|[[Mahaska County, Iowa|Mahaska]]\n|{{Coord|41.25|-92.51|name=Oskaloosa (Apr. 14, EF1)}}\n|0223\n|{{convert|1.3|mi|km|}}\n|This tornado was embedded in a larger area of straight-line wind damage, and caused minor to moderate damage along its path.\n|-\n|bgcolor=#{{storm colour|cat1}} | <big>'''EF1'''</big>\n|'''[[Hedrick, Iowa|Hedrick]]'''\n|[[Keokuk County, Iowa|Keokuk]]\n|{{Coord|41.17|-92.34|name=Martinsburg (Apr. 14, EF1)}}\n|0235\n|{{convert|3|mi|km|}}\n|10 homes were damaged in and around Hedrick, a baseball field in town was damaged, and many trees and power lines were downed. Grain bins and a machine shed were damaged, and a shed was destroyed. A police car was blown into a ditch as well.\n|-\n|colspan=\"7\" align=center| <small>Sources: [http://www.spc.noaa.gov/climo/reports/120414_rpts.html SPC Storm Reports for 04/14/12], [http://www.crh.noaa.gov/news/display_cmsstory.php?wfo=gid&storyid=81872&source=0 NWS Hastings], [http://www.crh.noaa.gov/ict/?n=april14th_icttor NWS Wichita], [http://www.crh.noaa.gov/news/display_cmsstory.php?wfo=ddc&storyid=81881&source=0 NWS Dodge City], [http://www.crh.noaa.gov/news/display_cmsstory.php?wfo=top&storyid=81885&source=0 NWS Topeka], [http://www.crh.noaa.gov/news/display_cmsstory.php?wfo=oax&storyid=81903&source=0 NWS Omaha], [http://www.crh.noaa.gov/lbf/?n=svrwxoutbreakapr14th2012 NWS North Platte], [http://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/stormevents/ NCDC Storm Events Database]</small>\n|-\n|}\n\n===April 15 event===\n{| class=\"wikitable collapsible\" width=\"100%\"\n!colspan=\"7\"|List of reported tornadoes - Sunday, April 15, 2012\n|-\n|<center>'''[[Enhanced Fujita scale|EF#]]'''</center> || <center>'''Location'''</center> || <center>'''County'''</center> || <center>'''Coord.'''</center> || <center>'''Time (UTC)'''</center> || <center>'''Path length'''</center> || <center>'''Comments/Damage'''</center>\n|-\n|colspan=\"7\" align=center|'''[[Nebraska]]'''\n|-\n|bgcolor=#{{storm colour|cat1}} | <big>'''EF1'''</big>\n|'''N of [[South Bend, Nebraska|South Bend]]'''\n|[[Cass County, Nebraska|Cass]], [[Sarpy County, Nebraska|Sarpy]]\n|{{Coord|41.01|-96.24|name=South Bend (Apr. 15, EF1)}}\n|0518\n|{{convert|1.9|mi|km|}}\n|Trees were downed and a few outbuildings were damaged along the path.\n|-\n|bgcolor=#{{storm colour|storm}} | <big>'''EF0'''</big>\n|'''W of [[Litchfield, Nebraska|Litchfield]]'''\n|[[Sherman County, Nebraska|Sherman]]\n|{